# LCM and HCF

## Topics Covered
- LCM (Least Common Multiple)
- HCF (Highest Common Factor)

## Formulas

LCM × HCF = Product of two numbers

## Examples

LCM of 12 and 18 = 36  
HCF of 12 and 18 = 6  

## Practice Done
Solved problems based on LCM and HCF concepts.

## Conclusion
Understood how to solve problems using LCM and HCF methods.
